nexml.meta:
Added polymorphs. There are some taxa comments concerning polymorphs for taxa that do not appear in the publication matrix. Also, several taxa (Chrysichthys mabusi, Parauchenoglanis punctatus, Ictalurus punctatus, Synodontis acanthomias, and Synodontis contracta) have taxa comments concerning polymorphs that occur in characters beyond character 93, which is where the publication matrix ends. Does anyone know where this data came from? AB 10/17/12
I checked the Mesquite file for this publication, and characters 94-113 were marked with an 'X' in the Inclusion column, so perhaps this data was intentionally left out. AB 10/17/12
